Most user data will have groups such as 'jira-administrators', 'jira-developers' and 'jira-users' in them. The Studio equivalent is the same, but dropping the 'jira-' prefix.

I believe the importer converts these group names in several places but seems to miss changing the project role actors. After performing an import it is still necessary to run the following SQL to correct it:

{code:SQL}
jira=> UPDATE projectroleactor SET roletypeparameter = REPLACE(roletypeparameter, 'jira-', '') WHERE roletypeparameter LIKE 'jira-%';
UPDATE 61
{code}

This means that projects may not have the correct permissions until this is done.

It should be done automatically as part of the import process.

